    "body": "### Problem\n\nFrom my chat with @luukvbaal in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33885#issuecomment-2868914361.\n\nIf I don't enable the new `vim._extui` settings and, as in the GIF, define a mapping like:\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set('n', '<Leader>xk', function()\n    vim.print('Foo\\nBar')\n    -- vim.notify('An error', vim.log.levels.ERROR)\n    -- vim.cmd('Git push --force-with-lease')\nend)\n```\nthen it can be seen that\n1. When executing the first line both `Foo` and `Bar` are shown\n2. When executing the notify line the `An error` is properly highlighted in red\n3. When using a command that streams output (such as fugitive's `Git push`) the message is properly formated upon completion\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5d9ac77c-1432-4539-9fb7-73e00b774658)\n\nOn the other hand if I enable the new grid with `require('vim._extui').enable({})` then, as in the GIF, we see that\n1. The first line echo is cutoff and a `spill` indicator is shown. We need to press `g<` to see full message. Personally I find this counterintuitive since as I user I'm explicitly requesting the print. \n2. When executing the notify line the  `An error` is not highlighted in red.  ✅\n3. When using a command that streams output the whole mangled/incomplete output is shown  ✅\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d595c8a8-0c83-4951-a8d5-a386819c8c2b)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSee above\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect the vim._extui to behave a bit more like the old message area.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-343+g1c96b72dfa\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo idea\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ntmux 3.5a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
